name: The Chronicle of the Clueless Age

description: Cartoonist Saverio Tenuta writes and paints a twisted tale of a masterless Samurai named Raido searching for clues to his bloody past in a feudal Japan ruled by spirits and beasts. Highly recommended for fans of Samura's BLADE OF THE IMMORTAL, Koike/Kojima's LONE WOLF & CUB, and HEAVY METAL magazine.

No need to venture into darkest Africa or the tropical jungles to satisfy your hunger for heat this vernal season. We've got it all right here, in our sizzling summer catalog! With a parade of plucky pulchritude in brass and leather, satin and silk, they'll put the steam in your steampunk faster than you can book passage on the next dirigible for the continent!

Ten years prior to the events of Darker than Black, an abnormal area dubbed "Hell's Gate" appeared in Tokyo,altering the landscape and sky. Shortly after its arrival, many people with various abilities began appearing. These abilities came at the cost of their humanity and the need to "pay the price", therefore, they were named Contractors. For every living Contractor, there was a fake star in the altered sky. Because of this, Contractors were referred to by the name of their given star. Although Contractor's made many public appearances, the truth of them and the sky were kept secret from the public. Many Contractors were hired by governments and secret organizations as assassins and spies. The ones who weren't, were often hunted down. The story revolves around Hei, a Contractor who works for the "Syndicate", a secret organization that tracks down and trains Contractors for assassination purposes.
